{{year-header}}
==June==
* '''[[11 June|11]]''' - German translator [[Walter Scherf]] is born.
* '''[[22 June|22]]''' - Voice acting legend [[Paul Frees]], who would voice several characters in the [[Rankin/Bass]] movies, is born.
* '''?''' - "[[The Happy Mariners]]" is published in ''[[The Stapeldon Magazine]]''.

==July==
* '''[[21 July|21]]''' - Tolkien is appointed to Readership in English Language at the [[University of Leeds]].
==August==
* '''[[16 August|16]]''' - [[Max Schuchart]], who would be the first to translate ''[[The Lord of the Rings]]'', is born.
* '''[[19 August|19]]''' - Composer [[Paul Kont]] is born.

==September==
* '''[[27 September|27]]''' - [[William Conrad]], voice actor who portrayed [[Denethor]] in [[The Return of the King (1980 film)|''The Return of the King'' (1980 film)]], is born.

==October==
* '''[[8 October|8]]''' - [[Nils Werenskiold]], the first Norwegian translator of ''[[The Lord of the Rings]]'', is born. 
* '''[[10 October|10]]''' - [[Victor Platt]], who would voice [[Samwise Gamgee|Sam]] in [[The Lord of the Rings (1955 radio series)|''The Lord of the Rings'' (1955 radio series)]], is born.
* '''[[22 October|22]]''' - [[Michael Tolkien]], Tolkien's second son, is born.
* '''[[30 October|30]]''' - [[Norman Bird]], who would voice [[Bilbo Baggins]] in [[The Lord of the Rings (1978 film)|''The Lord of the Rings'' (1978 film)]], is born.

==December==
* '''[[22 December|22]]''' - [[Father Christmas]] writes a [[Letters from Father Christmas|letter]] to [[J.R.R. Tolkien]]'s children.
==?==
* '''?''' - ''[[The Book of Fairy Poetry]]'' is published.
